lowLevelHttpTransport

public LowLevelHttpTransport lowLevelHttpTransport
Low level HTTP transport interface to use or null to use the default of java.net transport. See getLowLevelHttpTransport().

defaultHeaders

public final ArrayMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> defaultHeaders
Default headers mapping from header name to header value. These transport default headers are put into a request's headers when its build method is called.

defaultHeadersNoLogging

public final ArrayMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> defaultHeadersNoLogging
Default headers mapping from header name to header value for headers whose value must not be logged (for example authentication-related headers). These transport default headers are put into a request's headers when its build method is called.
